  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Deceptive Mailings Prevention Act of 1987</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">A bill to amend title 39 of the United States Code to designate as nonmailable matter solicitations for the purchase of products or services which are provided either free of charge or at a lower price by the Government and solicitations which are offered in terms implying Government connection or endorsement unless such matter contains conspicuous notice that the products or services offered are provided free of charge by the Government or that the Government does not endorse the products or services offered, and for other purposes.</title>
  </titles>
